caption: Ordered take out today from MCCB. Not only was the woman helping me out helpful, but she was very friendly too! Food was delicious and I will definitely be going there again. I highly recommend the pork belly and mango shrimp. I know they’re not open for dine in currently due to the pandemic but definitely consider taking out food from them!

This place hits the spot every single time. And they deliver their food hot and prompt every single time. Get the Sichuan boiled fish, pork belly, and the beef shumai, all so good. I have not had one dish that wasn't perfection form here actually, so order anything. Fantastic service and incredibly cheap too!
The food was extremely great with no complaints I say to the cooks and Staff,  keep up the good work!!!

Sure one should post pictures before you start eating but everything was so tasty.  Really good flavors. Good spice (especially on dumplings). Great take out spot.

Definitely our favorite Chinese place in Chinatown. We’ve tried them all and this is always our go to... so many great options and the dumplings are very tasty! Don’t miss out on this place!
My favorite place for chinese food. Will surely make a return trip. The bill was well within reason for the quality.

We visited here because of the high rating but were pretty disappointed. We ordered their signature fish. The fish was relatively small and overpriced between 3 people compared to the huge container it was put in. The fish had little meat and lots of extra seasonings. Service seemed slow at around 7:30-8 pm when we arrived. Other dishes like 干锅花菜were also average.
Chinese food here - yummy. Visited Sat afternoon. The service was friendly and sociable.

(Translated by Google) I was at this restaurant last August with my family. I LOVED IT, I love Chinese food. I can say that the Chinese food in this restaurant is the richest that I have ever tasted. We ordered several dishes to share and we were very surprised when our order was delivered, as the dishes are very large and we had a lot of food. The service was excellent, they were always waiting to serve us water and anything that was offered to us. Prices are very good and the menu has a great variety. This restaurant is next to Chinatown Square Plaza.  (Original) Estuve en este restaurante en agosto pasado con mi familia. LO AMÉ, la comida china me encanta. Puedo decir que la comida china de este restaurante es la más rica que he probado en toda mi vida. Pedimos varios platos para compartir y nos sorprendimos mucho cuando nos trajeron nuestra orden, ya que los platos son muy grandes y teníamos mucha comida. El servicio fue excelente, siempre estuvieron pendientes de servirnos agua y de cualquier cosa que se nos ofreciera. Los precios están muy bien y la carta tiene gran variedad. Put this place on your list to try!! It’s delicious high quality Chinese food, and they even have great vegetarian options. The customer service is top notch.
Mara steak is so good.
The new place to go in Chinatown! Excellent service. Food was equally great.

Good table service and delicious schezwan food. Had the dried chili rabbit, dry fried chili calamari & cucumbers, today. The servers are very helpful if you've not been to this restaurant before and can make helpful suggestions if your not familiar with the cuisine. The dishes are vegetarian adjustable which is really great!
Very good get the apple wood BBQ meal. Sooo yummy

Absolutely love this place!    The food is so delicious.   They have this spicy crispy beef and the authentic sweet and sour pork ribs.  So good.  Also you need to try the dessert .  It’s hard to explain but it has Chinese herbs in a sweet drink.   Service is excellent too.

The food here was great I absolutely loved it! I was however upset with the staff, my waitress took forever to bring us anything and hardly checked on us. They lack professional service. MCCB is my favorite Chinese restaurant!! Their foods are delicious, fresh and a great variety of food. I will totally recommend this place for someone who loves chinese food and is willing to try something new.

Excellent! Everything perfectly seasoned and very transparent/accurate about spiciness. Portions are generous and satisfying.
They always cancel your grubhub order and service is poor. I have lost money because of this place.
One of the better options in Chicago's Chinatown.

Hands down the best food I've had in Chinatown. The atmosphere is edgy, they give you metallic sharpies to sign your name on the walls which gives a fun, creative vibe. The service was above and beyond. We ordered the dry chili rub chicken and the honey black pepper chicken. A mix up happened and we got steak honey black pepper and they immediately re made my order and even let us keep the steak. It wasn't cheap after buying two beers for each  of us but it was worth every penny. Also our hotel key fell out of my boyfriends wallet and they totally saved us $50 by keeping it safe for us when we returned the next day. If you're having doubts about this place, just go. We definitely will eat here again.

Made reservations for my sons birthday and what can I say but I was great everyone so so friendly and attentive food was so good we started with some calamari shrimp dumplings appetizers and finished off with dan dan noodles (must try) the tofu was great as well for non meat eaters Orange chicken was so good and they made some salt and pepper chicken for my little guy as well that tasted awesome beef short rib very tasty and I ordered the whole fish little messy but I enjoyed it overall everything was wonderful thank you will be back. (FYI if your having a bday party call ahead they will have a cake ready for you)

Fabulous authentic (according to my Chinese colleague who took us) and diverse cuisine. Good service. Nice environment. Only thing I'd add is Peking Duck & alcoholic beverages... Definite check this place out - we ate a ton for 3 for lunch for just $80!
Big portions, good food, modern atmosphere. Bring a friend or two because there is plenty to eat!

If you came here and enjoyed the American Chinese food, I highly recommend their grilled fish!! The firsh is their specialty. Every other restaurant can make decent orange chicken, but this is the best grilled fish that I have tried in Chicago! The applewood smoke complements the dish super well.  They take reservations if you have a bigger party.  Be adventurous and try the fish!
Every meal has been amazing from the taste to the presentation.  The service is also wonderful.

Great authentic Chinese food in Chinatown.  We had the Spicy Calamari and the Apple Wood Charcoal Grill Lamb Rack.  You can tell them to adjust spice according to your preference.  Service is good also!
Great food and service!
Excellent dining experience. Staff is wonderful.  We had A cumin lamb dish and shrimp with okra.  Loved the food.

Since we came in the service was on point, nice people, very attentive and kind, the food WAS DELICIOUS. Really love this place. Even if you don't have a reservation they took us right in. Prices are really good for the big amount of food. A 100% Recommended.
Great food! Very fresh and tasty.
A great place for some delicious Chinese cuisine especially if you like spicy food you're in for a treat. It's usually busy so check on yelp if you can get on the waitlist or call them before going.

So first of all I would like to start out on how bad the service is. My family and I walked in and thought we would immediately be seated because the server was just standing there. It took about 2 minutes for us to be actually checked in. And even after that I thought that we would be seated immediately, but no. We had to wait 20 minutes for the table to be CLEARED. Just cleared. The restaurant itself is fairly small so I would say that that is WAY too long for us to be seated. Another thing I would like to complain about is about the restaurants menu quality. The papers themselves kept falling out of the binder and the thing that irked me the most was the amount of menus they gave us which was 3 when we had 7 people with us. I could understand if they had given us 6 menus because we had a child with us but no. They gave us three. You could even see more menus in plain sight that weren’t  being used. The food is actually pretty good, but the way it was served is awful. One of the orders that were served to us was served in a bowl that looked pretty nice but was in such bad quality. Other times the food that was supposed to be hot were cold and which is a sign of frozen food. When we ordered some rice, they gave us half of the bowl. Not 70 percent or 60 percent. Half. Which in my eyes is pretty disappointing. They don’t even give us napkins we had to ask for them. At this point this restaurant doesn’t even deserve more than 0 stars. I’d stop ranting but this place really needs to change. The bathroom was in terrible quality as well as a terrible location. I’ll start with the bathroom location. You’d have to walk through the kitchen and at that point you’d already be disappointed, but it gets worse. The bathroom door is open which is pretty disgusting. You walk in and the urinal is very unsanitary. Maybe to the point where it’s not safe to use. Then I go onto the sink. The knobs don’t even work and when it does the water is super cold. You can’t even get warm water. This is my final point on why you shouldn’t come here but there are many more flaws that aren’t fixed. The employees seem to be very careless at their job. They don’t give us napkins, enough menus, and to top it all off they watch us as we eat. I’m not talking about a quick glance to see if we need water or more rice. I’m talking about WATCHING. Which is a good enough reason to not come here, even without the other things. Anyways there are many other things, but in conclusion, this place treats you badly, violates your health and safety, and to top it all off is just a lazy place. IM WARNING YOU.
The menu offers authentic Sechuan cousine - tender and with that amazing Sechuan pepper flavor. On top of the great food, this place also has very frienfly and competent waiters.
Fantastic food

I wanted to try some spicy food with some friends. We ended up trying this place next to our favorite place, Hing Kee. The food here hit the spot for my spice craving. The dan dan noodles was a perfect spice level for the whole party. It's the numbing spice but it still retained a lot of flavor. I was glad that the server let me take the shot before she mixed it up. We had the mapo tofu with ground pork next. One friend had to tap out since it was significantly spicy. I loved it. I just wish it would have came with some rice. Luckily, we also ordered the traditional yang zhou fried rice. It didn't have a lot of salt or overpowering flavor so it actually paired well with the mapo tofu. The orange Fanta bottle was one with cane sugar so my friend enjoyed that. I would come back here again to try some different things.
The food was excellent.

Go check out this small diner located in chinatown square. Prices were reasonable and service was exceptional. I would consider this to be above average oriental chow. I tried the pork belly which was crispy and mixed with different vegetables. The dish had a real good kick of spice. The lady tried short ribs which was just as good with a rich flavor. Sweet and sour soup was interesting. I get lots of sweet and sour soups in the suburbs but that taste much different. The soup had a real sour punch to it which I have never tasted before. Not sure if it's a good or bad thing, kind of indifferent and still deciding. Crab rangoon had a real nice consistency inside. Dishes came with a bowl of sticky white rice. Also they let you write on the walls with markers, pretty cool.  Try the pork belly and you wont regret it.  CHEERS !!!

(Translated by Google) Very good Chinese restaurant, very authentic. It is not easy to come to a foreign country to eat authentic Chinese food. The smile of the waiter's sister is very warm.  (Original) 非常好的中餐馆，很正宗。来到异国他乡吃到正宗中餐还是不容易的，服务员妹妹的笑容很温暖。

I highly recommend this place if you visit Chicago. I went because of all the great reviews I read on Yelp. Certainly worth it! I ordered the chef specials Szechuan stir fried chicken and it certainly did not disappoint. Also the eggrolls were delicious.

Wholesome Hunan food with a good amount of options for lunch. I love the fish in ginger sauce. I always feel good after eating here, not something that happens after eating at all MCCB Chicago 时尚食谱. Very nice dining room ambience. Come in to get away from the maddening crowd.

Easily one of my favorite spots in Chinatown. As their name indicates "modern" they do have their unique touch on the main traditional dishes they have to offer. Compared to other places in the plaza, this is definitely much cleaner, service is pretty good, and there's even a 2nd level where they host larger parties / groups. I absolutely love their noodles here. Can't go wrong whether it's a traditional beef chow mein or some dan dan noodles, you won't be disappointed. The boiled fish is also pretty good, and I can appreciate it's mellowed out a bit so you don't have to worry about your face melting off. Be sure to hold onto your receipt as they do offer coupons to Bingo Tea a few doors down in case you're craving some boba after a meal from here.  'Til next time!
Get the fantail shrimp, pork dumplings, cumin lamb. All fantastic! Fish (tilapia) is ok, has a strong "muddy" flavor that spice and broth do well to mask.

What an experience! Best. Crab. Rangoon. Ever. Highlight was the spicy dumplings. If you see food as an experience, you must try the steak pot. Ours was ribeye, scallops, veggies and garlic deliciousness. Way more food than the three of us could consume!

Just took the water taxi to Chinatown and tried MCCB for the first time.  Our party of three enjoyed the hot & sour soup and chicken rolls for apps but we really loved the chicken stir-fry, cumin flank steak and peppered short ribs.  We all like our food with a kick and it fulfilled our spice need.  The cumin was not over done as it is at some restaurants.  The ambiance  was nice and the place was very clean (which isn't the case at many Chinatown restaurants).  We all left satiated and said we will definitely be back.

MCCB is literally my favorite Chinese restaurant that I have ever been to! It is located in the Chinatown Neighborhood of Chicago which really adds to the experience in my opinion. Everything about this place is authentic and I live for that type of experience!  The staff is fantastic and take great care of their customers. You will never be without a filled drink.  I highly recommend the Egg Drop Soup, Egg Rolls and Spicy Garlic Chicken! Portions are huge, so come hungry and consider picking a couple things to share. Run out of rice? Just ask for more, they’ll be happy to accommodate!  Definitely check this place out when visiting Chicago! Prices are fantastic for being in the Chicago area!

Spot on! Spot on - ambience Spot on - food Spot on - service I couldn't make a reservation online because it was booked so I called in and the man on the phone was really kind and gave us a last minute reservation. Immediately you could feel the hospitality and once I got to the restaurant, it was no different. The staff is welcoming, busy and always moving around with a smile. The feel of the place is easy, light and manageable though there are a lot of people coming in and out all the time. The food measures up to everything I have heard and read about this place. We don't like wasting food so only ordered sharing items that were filling without feeling bloated and it was delicious. Food at MCCB is actually one of the better Chinese food I have had in a very long time. I cannot wait to visit again and try their other many menu items!
Surprisingly good Sichuan style Chinese food. The grilled fish is the best I had in USA, and I have tried many during the past years in different cities.

Excellent restaurant and exceptional service! Would certainly recommend if you are looking for a pleasant spot to eat in Chinatown. The Cheng Du dumplings were terrific -- great flavor and not overpowering spice for those that want a little chili taste but not a running nose. The honey pepper steak was delightful as well as the dry chili chicken. Everything was perfect! Our favorite part was the service. Kevin, our server, was beyond helpful and friendly!! Thanks so much MCCB!
(Translated by Google) Delicious and cheap Very good fish. And very good price.  (Original) 好吃且便宜 Very good fish. And very good price.

Second trip and it was great again. The servers are extremely friendly and attentive. The food was fresh and delicious. Highly recommend the spicy shrimp appetizer and the pot stickers. The dining area is small in comparison to other restaurants in Chinatown but the decor is very welcoming. A can’t miss spot!

Want to give them five stars but I hold that for my absolute favorite spots. With that said MCCB is a great vibrant place to dine. Above average with quality modern style. We could choose from our go to favs as well as try something new. Definitely an interesting menu with a well represented variety to choose from. We were extremely happy to finally try this location on our tour of Chinatown restaurants. We started with the Dry Chili Calamari, Crab Rangoon & Sweet and Spicy Beef Shumai. Followed by the Crisy Mango Shrimp (which were great), Jumbo Shrimp Chow Mein, Fresh Garlic Tong Choi (Delicious), Dry Chili Flank Steak , Clams with Black Bean Sauce (Demolished in Minutes) & Salt And Pepper Short Ribs (My Fav). Our sever was very engaged in our dining experience making sure we had everything we needed and wanted. Only thing I can say more is I want to go back.

Excellent Sichuan dishes, reasonable prices, and very friendly service. Enjoyed the Ma Po tofu, Mei Zhou baby back ribs, the boiled Sichuan beef, and the sauteed bok choi. (Note, as is appropriate to the style,  all of these dishes, with the exception of the Bok Choi, are spicy. Not for the feint of heart.)

chinese food and the setting here is very good. Prices are appropriate.

MCCB hits the spot whenever I'm craving spicy Chinese food! I've been here twice and every time has been such a great experience! First off, they probably have the best service in Chinatown! The waiters are very attentive and thoughtful.Our absolute favorite dish is the dan dan pork fried rice! It's not labeled as a spicy dish, but c'mon now, you're at a Sichuan restaurant, how can it not be spicy?! The portion is humongous. The sauce is fragrant and savory! They also use fermented soybeans, which adds a nice flavor. I recently tried the boiled flank steak and the Chengdu spicy dumplings. YESSS to both! The boiled flank steak is pretty much spicy braised beef. The sauce is numbingly spicy but so delicious!! The portion is quite generous. The chengdu dumplings are not as spicy as I had expected. It's more of a sweet chili taste. You seriously cannot go wrong with anything here!
Absolutely delicious food, definitely my new favorite place in Chinatown. The service could improve a tad bit.
Dishes were fantastic. We had the dry Chili chicken and the hot pot. Highly recommend both.
Food and service were excellent.

The fish was not fresh when I took a bite, but my bf said that was fine, he thought it not big deal, so we did not complain about it. But when I got to hotel, I felt sick whole night. Ruined my whole day. So disappointed. Service is ok.

We ordered a couple of different dishes starting with the cold cucumber, I would say its one of my favorite dish. We got the cold meat next and it was surprisingly good? We also ordered 2 fried pot stickers: pork & chives and shrimp & chives both were definitely pretty good and crispy however it would break apart like after one bite. We also tried the steamed dumpling and it was pretty okay, I would prefer the fried one. Lastly, we tried their braised soup and that was pretty nice to end the meal with hot soup. The meat was very tender and noodles were good as well.  We would definitely come back to try other dishes.

The food here is amazing. Staff are very courteous and rhey can prepare the food according to your requirements.  They could improve a bit on their drinks selection but I think you can BYOB to the place. Over all this is one of my favorite places in Chinatown

chinese food, mmm, so good. I had a brother come into town and asked me to take him back here. It has a cool interior.
Really tasty food. We didn't get a tableside grill, but on seeing other people's I kind of regretted it. The spicy garlic eggplant was a major highlight.
Great choices, and style of layout for the menu. My favorite dish has to be the peppered chicken. Flavor bombs everywhere! Accommodates bigger parties in the upstairs area.

Food is hot, fresh,  and delicious.  The calamari melts in your mouth, it's so good! Service is also fantastic.  I must've had my water cup filled like 7 times while I ate. Cant go wrong with as anything on the menu.

Excellent food in Chicago's Chinatown neighborhood.  Friendly staff and vibrant atmosphere, will definitely return.

I had the pork in the garlic sauce and asked them to add some spinach. My meal was light on the garlic. When I found the few bits of  ginger, each one brought a smile to my face. I then asked them the add the spinach to the pork and garlic sauce. This cost me $3, which I feel was fairly priced.  My water glass was constantly full.
Amazing food. We loved the garlic eggplant and the cucumber appetizer. The Italian sodas are delicious and really fun and festive. I would recommend making a reservation, especially on the weekend.
This is my new go-to place in Chinatown. Tons of variety on the menu made it hard to choose but what I ended up getting (Black Pepper Honey Beef) blew me away. I will definitely be coming back!

This place is so delicious! Went here with a vegetarian crew and there were so many options! The service was extremely friendly and we loved the atmosphere. Growing up, it was always our parents who made the Chinatown decisions and this restaurant was a great first "adulthood" decision, haha.  We ended up ordering their Chengdu Style Hot Pot where they were able to replace the meat-stock with water, but don't worry all the flavor was there! It was also a HUGE serving (pictured below). This is truly in the Sichuan spirit, so if you're looking ma-la and bold flavor -- MCCB is the place to be!  With the option of Vegetarian dishes, great flavor, friendly staff -- highly recommend! This is also a great place for meatatarians as we saw all our neighboring tables order as elaborate meaty dishes. Perhaps MCCB could be your next middle ground for both!  We will be visiting again! :)

As Chinese food getting more and more popular in America, it is quite important to provide customers the most authentic and creative dishes, and ultimately, all of these dishes must be special, representative and delicious. That said is the mission for team MCCB (Modern Chinese Cook Book), founded by four experienced and energetic food enthusiasts who have been in Chinese food industry for over ten years.  The top specialty from us is Charcoal Grilled Whole Fish, a street style food originated from Chongqing, China. We charcoal grill the wild caught tilapia first, then soak the fish in a hot chili broth filled pan, served on table on top of stylish and exquisitely carved stand, with continual charcoal grill as a must process to enjoy this dish. There is also option to select your favorite meat or vegetables to cook in the broth, which will bring you a fantastic exciting taste beside the tender whole fish.  When going back to standard, our special Sichuan and Canton style cuisine will offer you the most delicate traditional and innovative selections including Iron Basket Chili Prawn, Kung Pao Chicken, Mapo Tofu, Icy Okra, Crispy Lemon or Pina Colada flavored shrimps, with all these preliminary hint of our creations, we truly expect your visit as adventure to explore the great modern Chinese food, and team MCCB is dedicated to ensure the best of your experience.
